        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="1017" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1017">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/11–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-17T13:00:00-05:00">November 17, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2123. Pls inform FonOff that we have given careful and sympathetic consideration
                    to Ital request for revision of armistice regime and are prepared to accede to
                    Ital request provided other govts signatory to Armistice concur. Accordingly,
                    Dept is informing other signatories of American position and inquiring re their
                    attitude.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
